headline: PayPal Stock Surges on Earnings Beat, OpenAI Partnership. Making Sense of It All.
summary: PayPal Holdings  beat Wall Street’s expectations for earnings and revenue in the third quarter and raised its guidance for the year, citing “broad-based profitable growth” across its various lines of business.  Shares of PayPal rose 11% to $78 in premarket trading.  The company broadly beat projections.
